.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The DG discretization converges optimally with order 
\begin_inset Formula $O\left(h^{p+1}\right)$
\end_inset

 in the 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{2}\left(\Omega\right)$
\end_inset

 norm, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert y-y_{\mathrm{exact}}\right\Vert _{L_{2}\left(\Omega\right)}$
\end_inset

, when no interior faces are present in the domain, but it converges sub-optimal
ly with order 
\begin_inset Formula $O\left(h^{p+\nicefrac{1}{2}}\right)$
\end_inset

 in the 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{2}\left(\Omega\right)$
\end_inset

 norm due to the numerical flux at interior faces.
 Furthermore, since the discretization is adjoint consistent, we expect
 super-optimal convergence of the order 
\begin_inset Formula $2p+1$
\end_inset

 for a functional output
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Har13"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 In the context of ODE integration, we are interested in the behavior of
 the error of the terminal condition, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|y\left(t_{f}\right)-y_{\mathrm{exact}}\left(t_{f}\right)\right|$
\end_inset

 and can therefore expect the error to exhibit 
\begin_inset Formula $O\left(h^{2p+1}\right)$
\end_inset

 super-convergence
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Bau95,Har13"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Finally, DGODE is stiffly A-stable for all polynomial degrees 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Del81,Bau95"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
\begin_inset Formula $hp$
\end_inset

-adaptivity 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:dg-ode-hp-adaptivity"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We adaptively control both the time step, 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

, and the degree of the polynomial approximation, 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

, to ensure efficient integration of the nonlinear system and that the solution
 achieved is within a desired accuracy.
 The the norm of the local error estimate
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mathrm{err}_{h}=\left\Vert \frac{\mathcal{R}_{i}\left(y\right)}{\epsilon_{\mathrm{abs}}+\epsilon_{\mathrm{rel}}\left|y_{i}\right|}\right\Vert \label{eq:dg-ode-error}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

is used to define the nonlinear convergence criteria, which is given as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mathrm{err}_{h}<1\label{eq:dg-ode-convergence-criteria}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,\ldots,n$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{\mathrm{abs}}=10^{-6}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{\mathrm{rel}}=10^{-12}$
\end_inset

 are user specified absolute and relative tolerances.
 If
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dg-ode-convergence-criteria"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 is not satisfied within 
\begin_inset Formula $n=5$
\end_inset

 iterations, the time step is reduced by a factor of ten.
 Otherwise, we estimate the accuracy of the solution and adapt the polynomial
 degree of the approximation accordingly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to determine if adaptation of the polynomial degree is necessary,
 we apply a residual based a posteriori error estimation
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Har13"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 This approach has proved to be simple and robust.
 The the residual based error estimate is defined in terms of the interior
 cell residual and the interface residual:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\mathcal{R}_{i}^{p}\left(y\right) & = & \sum_{\kappa\in\mathcal{T}}\left(y',\varphi_{i}\right)_{\kappa}-\sum_{\kappa\in\mathcal{T}}\left(\mathcal{S}\left(y\right),\varphi_{i}\right)_{\kappa},\label{eq:dg-ode-residual-p-adaptation-cell}\\
r_{i}^{p}\left(y\right) & = & \sum_{\epsilon\in\mathcal{E_{\partial}}}\left(h_{\partial}\left(y^{+},n\right),\varphi_{i}^{+}\right)_{\mathcal{E}_{\partial}}+\sum_{\epsilon\in\mathcal{E_{I}}}\left(h\left(y^{+},y^{-},n\right),\left\llbracket \varphi_{i}\right\rrbracket \right)_{\mathcal{E_{I}}}.\label{eq:dg-ode-residual-p-adaptation-boundary}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

In the case of the single-element, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega=\kappa=\left(t_{0},t_{f}\right)$
\end_inset

, spectral discretization, Equation
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dg-ode-residual-p-adaptation-boundary"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 reduces to
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
r_{i}^{p}\left(y\right)=\left(\left(y_{0}-y^{+}\right),\varphi_{i}^{+}\right)_{\mathcal{E}_{0}},\label{eq:dg-ode-residual-p-adaptation-boundary-one-element}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where the only interface contribution is due to the inflow boundary condition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The norm of the local error estimate for 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

-refinement is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mathrm{err}_{p}=\left\Vert \mathcal{R}_{i}^{p}\left(y\right)\right\Vert _{L^{2}\left(\Omega\right)}+\left\Vert r_{i}^{p}\left(y\right)\right\Vert _{L^{2}\left(\Omega\right)},\label{eq:dg-ode-error-p}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and the accuracy criteria is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mathrm{err}_{p}<\epsilon_{p},\label{eq:dg-ode-convergence-criteria-p}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{p}=10^{-6}$
\end_inset

 is a user specified tolerance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the nonlinear solver converges, i.e.
 
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dg-ode-convergence-criteria"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 is satisfied within 
\begin_inset Formula $n=5$
\end_inset

 iterations, and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dg-ode-convergence-criteria-p"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 is satisfied, the solution is updated and a new time-step is determined
 using Gustafsson's method
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Hai96"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
dt_{i+1}=\left(\frac{kdt_{i}}{dt_{i-1}}\left(\frac{\mathrm{err}_{i}^{2}}{\mathrm{err}_{i-1}}\right)^{-\frac{1}{4}}\right)dt_{i}\label{eq:dg-ode-time-step-gustafsson}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $k=0.9$
\end_inset

 is a user defined ratio of consecutive time steps.
\end_layout

\end_inset

